721026f-c.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 52nd Street
721026f-c.text:
(1)
Swedish Methodist Episcopal Church, Lexington Ave., at the S.W.
corner of 52nd Street.
May 3, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, showing the 52nd Street side. Story of church in:
''New York Times'' January, 29, 1937, page 38.
January 24, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(3)
Similar to No. 1, but more extensive northward. Note the 1-story
business and theatre building that is replacing the Church. North of
same is the Y.w.C.A.
October 12, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPEODUCEIONS.
